      "author": "overmoro",
      "description": "## What's new\n\n### Paragraph highlighting\n\nBottom-left corner button toggles highlight mode. When active (yellow), tap any paragraph to wrap it in \\`==...==\\` - persisted to the source file. Tap the same paragraph again to remove the highlight. Non-paragraph blocks (headings, lists, callouts, code fences) are not tappable. Scroll position is preserved through every highlight write.\n\n### Scripture tap-to-expand\n\nBible references in your sermon text are automatically detected and shown with a dotted underline (e.g. \\`John 3:16\\`, \\`Rom 8:28-30\\`, \\`1 Cor 13:4-7\\`). Tap any reference to expand the passage inline from your vault CSB files. Tap the expanded passage (or the reference again) to collapse. Verse text is cached in memory after first load for instant re-expansion.\n\nReferences inside code blocks and callouts are intentionally skipped. Non-existent references show a small inline error rather than crashing the view. Cross-chapter ranges are deferred to v0.4.0.\n\n### CSB folder path setting now active\n\nThe Bible folder path setting (previously a disabled stub) is now live. Default: \\`30_Knowledge/Theology/Bible/CSB\\`. Change it in Settings > Preach MD > Scripture if your Bible files live elsewhere.",
      "downloadCount": 1,
